<span id="freeTextContainer11726364483453325771">Not as unputdownable as the other Pendergast novels thus far in the series. Edit. Second reading in as many years and having read 18 books in this series, I can confirm, that Brimstone is excellent, not as exciting as Relic Still Life with Crows or City of Endless Night, but still an enjoyable and clever experience.</span>

