<div id="review_3009455834" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3009455834" />
    <a title="❀ Crystal ✿ -  PEACE ☮ LOVE ♥ BOOKS " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10734393-crystal---peace-love-books"><img alt="❀ Crystal ✿ -  PEACE ☮ LOVE ♥ BOOKS " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396916584p2/10734393.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3009455834?book_show_action=true">Nov 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="❀ Crystal ✿ -  PEACE ☮ LOVE ♥ BOOKS " class="user" itemprop="url" name="❀ Crystal ✿ -  PEACE ☮ LOVE ♥ BOOKS " href="/user/show/10734393-crystal---peace-love-books">❀ Crystal ✿ -  PEACE ☮ LOVE ♥ BOOKS </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10734393-crystal---peace-love-books?shelf=2020-read-list">2020-read-list</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3009455834" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16889766056952824522">After the dryness of book four I was so excited to jump into this book. Not only is Pendergast back in NYC, he also once again teams up with Lt. D&apos;Gosta and Captain Hayward. The book hooked me right from the start with a maid finding the microwaved body of her boss. All signs pointed to some type of demonic ritual and I was so eager to see how the authors would spin it. I can never be too sure with where they take things especially with someone like Pendergast involved. Body after body piles up </span>
  <span id="freeText16889766056952824522" style="display:none">After the dryness of book four I was so excited to jump into this book. Not only is Pendergast back in NYC, he also once again teams up with Lt. D'Gosta and Captain Hayward. The book hooked me right from the start with a maid finding the microwaved body of her boss. All signs pointed to some type of demonic ritual and I was so eager to see how the authors would spin it. I can never be too sure with where they take things especially with someone like Pendergast involved. Body after body piles up and the action continues on while D'Gosta &amp; Pendergast try to get to the bottom of things, even becoming world travelers, when the case takes them to Italy. I was a bit shocked by the villain, he was a character who seemed so obvious, too involved and helpful that I brushed his involvement off. Apparently he was a lot more talented at acting than he let on as he and his associate really got the drop on these two. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I knew Pendergast wouldn't be killed but I was floored when this guy got the better of him. That doesn't really happen, Pendergast is always one step ahead, or he was... until now. After being walled in in the basement, D'Gosta truly believes Pendergast is dead and gone. While he does avenge him (which was awesome), it's not until a mystery man with dual colored eyes appears and begins chipping at the brick that things really started coming together. I imagine this is his long lost and sociopathic brother. Someone who possibly knows all there is to know about Pendergast and probably the only person with the ability to outwit him. Either way I am here for it and so ready to see what's next. I surely didn't see Hayward and D'Gosta hooking up and certainly didn't expect a crazy preacher to rile up NYC the way he did. I really wondered if the villain was a demon and if there wasn't more going on than met the eye. In fact I'm a bit bummed that it was just a deranged human bad guy lol. The dork inside me was also so excited to be revisiting the Cabinet of Curiosities home because it's just so fascinating. Also now there is a young girl whose been found hiding in the home, I imagine a leftover test subject that is unfortunately immortal but a wealth of information. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> Things left on a tense end and poor D'Gosta leaves Italy assuming the worst. At least on a personal level things seem to be getting better for him, I only hope he learns of his friends rebirth sooner rather than later because Pendergast is going to need all the help he can get.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16889766056952824522" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


