        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2985997817" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10725764253284826013">3.5 stars. Although not a high rating I still enjoyed the book immensely, Pendergast books are like that. You can always be assured of something riveting and weird/strange/bizarre. Although the fifth Pendergast book it is the first in the Diogenes trilogy. Diogenes is Pendergast&apos;s brother and a psychopathic killer. He has something evil planned and only Pendergast can stop him. But will he live long enough?</span>
  <span id="freeText10725764253284826013" style="display:none">3.5 stars. Although not a high rating I still enjoyed the book immensely, Pendergast books are like that. You can always be assured of something riveting and weird/strange/bizarre. Although the fifth Pendergast book it is the first in the Diogenes trilogy. Diogenes is Pendergast's brother and a psychopathic killer. He has something evil planned and only Pendergast can stop him. But will he live long enough?</span>
